benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails - Add account email

covered: POST method coverage: Happy path TC01 demonstrates 201 creation, response as an AccountEmail object array, and Location header; TC02 covers optional headers (X-Killbill-Reason, X-Killbill-Comment); AccountId path parameter validation covered via TC07 (invalid format), TC08 (missing), and TC09 (non-existent) with appropriate 400/404 responses; Authorization scenarios covered by TC13 (missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy) and TC14 (unauthorized access); Validation tests covered by TC10 (malformed JSON), TC11 (missing required fields), and TC12 (invalid email format); Edge cases covered by TC06 (extra fields) and TC18 (extra query parameters); Account state variations covered by TC03 (no existing emails) and TC04 (existing emails); Large payloads TC16 and empty payload TC17; External dependencies and resilience TC15 (503 service unavailable) and TC19 (slow DB); Recovery TC25; Unicode/regression TC21; Backward compatibility TC22; Security tests TC23 (SQL injection) and TC24 (XSS); Integration TC26; Accessibility TC27; Concurrency TC20; Large set of acceptance criteria including integration, error handling, and documented behavior.
gaps: Duplicate submission handling (adding the same email twice) is not explicitly tested (idempotency/duplicate handling).
Internal server error (500) scenarios are not explicitly tested (only 503 covered).
Rate limiting / throttling scenarios are not tested.
Caching behavior (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache validation are not tested.
Edge case with insufficient privileges beyond unauthorized (403) is not fully explored.
Content negotiation / Accept header variations are not tested.
Tests for invalid or unsupported Accept headers are not tested.
recommendations: Add a test for duplicate email submission to verify idempotency or proper error handling.
Add tests simulating 500 Internal Server Error or database failure.
Introduce rate limiting tests to validate behavior under bursts.
Add tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache validation.
Include tests for insufficient privileges beyond basic unauthorized (403) scenarios.
Add tests for content negotiation with various Accept headers and unsupported values.
